I want readers to come to a place that has as much scripture as is needed to study academically and intensely. Which is why there are resources for Greek Interlinear and English bible dictionaries. 



This work was inspired by Scripture especially Daniel and John.
	
Daniel because some early church fathers interpret 12:4 as "going to and fro" through scripture.
This resource should reduce the to and fro. Scripture information will just be "there." And thus "knowledge will increase."
	
John for his simplicity. He tries to communicate everything you need to know. 
	
John also notes that Jesus said he is the "light of the world" and the "Word." This has inspired the dark mode default. The Word is "Light"(white text, technically ultra light grey for vision limitation) and since God the person represents a hidden/unrevealed nature the background color is black. This is also very good for the eyes and those who get headaches from computer screens. 
	
	
	
How to use:
	
This page is best viewed on a 4k UHD monitor that is 27"-50." It will still work on older 1080p monitors but the experience is lacking. This should be fine for ordinary users. In 4k mode however, this leaves enough room for two instances of the webpage to run side by side for quad panel viewing of the bible. Or for external sources. This isn't an elaborate expense in 2026, 4k TV prices are down to a record low and potatoes are up. (revelation 6:6)
	
To increase font size locate the drop down menu in the top left of the screen "12px." For really small and large fonts use the CTRL and + or - keys on the numberpad.
	
In order to search the text files you are currently on:
	1) click the body of text you are searching
	2) Hold CTRL key on keyboard and press F. CRTL+F
	3) At the bottom of the page a search bar will appear. 
	Just type the word and use the arrows.
	
The Navigation menu can be resized via the small triangle at the bottom right corner of the menu. (click, hold and drag left or right)

The best way to "scroll" down the pages is not the mouse. It's the keyboard. HOME takes you to the beginning of a page, END to the end, PG DOWN and PG UP "scroll" the page fast, the ARROW keys "scroll" the page slowly. 

This webpage also provides one of the best ways to get a clean copy of text for the purpose of formal writing. When you "copy" there is no background markup. Meaning: It does not interfer with the text formatting on your editor of choice such as Word, Blogs, others. 
	
How to find the words that Jesus said without red text markup? Read the text locate the words(or similar): And Jesus Said
	
If you want red highlights or any practical color there is a drop down menu in the top left. Default is green. Inspired by classic computers that only displayed green. To select multiple blocks of texts hold CTRL. The page only supports one color highlight mode. There are no plans to change this. Use your preferred color. 
	
One easy way to cite this webpage is with screenshots. The title of each book has been included at the top of the page for ease of use.
